==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[νεκρόπολις]]''' (''nekropolis'') "a city of the dead", from '''[[νεκρός]]''' (''nekros'') "dead" + '''[[πόλις]]''' (''polis'') "city".

===Noun===
#a large [[cemetery]], esp. one that is elaborately built in an ancient city

